cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.RO 

This paper deals with robust fitting problems in computer vision, which is a common topic in the computer vision community. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes novel algorithms for optimization, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithms involve solving convex subproblems, which could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with estimation problems with geometric residuals, which could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics).
